# CADS Design System Rules

- Before building or updating a CADS library component, run the `cads-parity-qa` workflow from spec pull through deterministic visual recapture; it is not an end-only checklist.
- Import components from `@codeai/cads-react` only (icons from `@codeai/cads-react/icons`).
- Import `@codeai/cads-variables/variables.css` once at the app root.
- Use semantic color variables (e.g. `--background-brand-primary`) — never hard-coded hex, never invent color aliases, never use a `--ds-` prefix.
- Brand tokens for CTAs/links; selected tokens for filled selected chrome; focused for focus rings.
- Prefer CADS typography variables (`--font-heading`, `--text-body-*`, etc.) over raw px.
- Control heights via component `size` props (`large` / `medium` / `small` / `extraSmall`) — do not invent heights.
- Consult `cadsManifest` before adding or inventing props.
